node.text:
Broke: Stocks are falling, you panic sell

Woke: You know people are panicking, you wait it out, investment comes back up

G’s: Everyone is freaking out selling off. I’m shopping at a discount, buy more income & get better prices 

Full video on my YouTube. 

To give you a practical example I like $OKE at $50 and I’ll hold till it returns back to $71 

If you understand this concept drop a 💰 in the comments and share this in your story. I got a gift for someone who shares it

node.text:
Started the week with a $4,000 dividend payment, ending the week with a $8,000 dividend payment 

The name of the game is Get money, buy income. That’s the whole game, that’s the strategy I’m going to live, work & die by. 

And once I’m dead my family will keep getting the rent payments and dividends. 

Grab cyber money, $40 for the next 500 then it’s back to $199

node.title: $8,000 dividend payment to end the week

node.text:
Play long term games, win long term prizes 

Wanna know why I post what I’m buying and how much I’m buying? 

It’s not to show off or prove I have money

It’s not to convince people to buy what I’m buying, invest in what I’m investing in 

It’s to prove the concept of buying low 

Everyone says buy low sell high, but in reality all I see is people buy high and then panic sell low 

As my investments go lower in price I’m more likely to buy it not less likely 

If I / believe ETH is going to $5k per coin why wouldn’t I buy more of it when the price goes lower? 

It’s common sense to me and when it becomes common sense to you, your investing life will change 

I put my money where my mouth is every day of the week and I’ll never tell people to do what I’m not doing myself 

All of my stock and crypto buys are posted in @wealthsquad_ 

It’s an educational group but whenever I make a move, I tell the squad about it. 

Everybody eats. 

Abundance my niggas, abundance
